<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib special">247. Linton, Harold. Color Model Environments: Color and Light in Three-Dimensional Design. New York: Van Nostrand Reinhold, 1985. 250 pp. Index, bibl., B/W illus., color illus. ISBN 0-442-25893-3. </p><p class="annot">This excellent text begins with an overview of design elements andbasic materials and techniques. It features a unique section that relates color and light to three-dimensional design principles. In turn, this information is applied to the planning processes and models used by architecture and design students and professionals. Many fine color illustrations enrich this handsome and useful book. </p></div>
